A little comparison between notification agents alternatives (please add stuff here):

* GnusNotify allows you to select which groups you want to include in the report; see above for how
* [GnusNotify gnus-notify+] works with a timer, and each time it runs, slows down your Emacs for a moment
* [GnusNotify gnus-notify+] shows only a total count of unread messages, whereas GnusNotify shows the group names which contain unread messages but doesn't tell you how many
* GnusBiff is „too primitive“ according to its own description
* GnusDesktopNotify can be configured per-group and can call any arbitrary program in response to new mail
* …

